                <param name="widgettype" value="shortplayer" />
            </object>
        </section>
        <p data-uuid="c84874463fe3454c9cfc82cdf544a337">In
            the 1060s a Muslim group called the Almoravids (al-muh-RAH-vuhdz) attacked
            Ghana in an effort to force its leaders to convert to Islam. The Almoravids
            weakened Ghana’s empire and cut off many trade&#160;routes.</p>
        <p data-uuid="295dbc0d3e834643bf955b5285d0c83a">
            Without
            its trade, Ghana could not support its empire, and the empire eventually fell.
            The influence of Islam, however, remained strong. By the late 1400s Islam would
            become the most practiced religion in the region.</p>
